                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>1</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="21297" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 13 Dec 2006 05:04:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s a bit of a pain that JasperReports espects specifically typed values there and doesn&apos;t do any built-in conversion from Strings... After all, the expected value type depends on the specific property key, and cannot be reliably determined at runtime (as far as I see).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="21299" author="robh" created="Wed, 13 Dec 2006 09:21:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually Spring 2.0 &lt;b&gt;does&lt;/b&gt; support this conversion of values but often it needs to be extended. We can only reliably convert &apos;true&apos; and &apos;false&apos;. Users can override convertParameterValue in any JR view class to perform custom conversion (remember to call super....)&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Rob&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="21441" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sat, 23 Dec 2006 05:03:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since there are quite a few standard JasperReports parameters that take an integer value, I&apos;ve added a default check whether we got a String value that starts with a digit, which we&apos;ll then automatically convert to an Integer (keeping it as String value if number conversion fails). This seems to work quite well...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
